            <h2>Windsor Pizzerias</h2>
                        <p>Madonna, residents on Vancouver Island, and soldiers in Vietnam share an unexpected connection: their request for Windsor-style pizza. Windsor has a rich business history, shaped by its proximity to Detroit and its relationship to the North American auto industry. However, pizza-makers in Windsor have created a unique, internationally recognized industry that thrives on local, family-run restaurants. Windsor pizza, is known for its shredded pepperoni, canned mushrooms, Galati cheese, and crust dusted with cornmeal. Windsor Pizza companies have asserted a uniquely Canadian identity that counters American influence.</p>

            <p>
                Windsor has many pizzerias that helped create a legacy of internationally recognized pizza. Antoninos, Armandos, Capri, Naples, and Arcata are just few amoung the Windsor pizza tradtion. Hardwork, consistency, local ingredient sourcing, and family ownership are buisness practices that have allowed these companies to thrive. Italian immigrants who created these pizzerias throughout Windsor's history helped carry these pracitices. These buisness histories highlight what made Windsor Pizza a source of identity for Windsorites.
            </p>
